Event Rooms
At Ardea Country Club, our event rooms are designed to transform your special occasions into unforgettable moments. Whether you're hosting a wedding, corporate gathering, or social event, our exquisite spaces provide the perfect backdrop. Elevate your events with the elegance and versatility of our event rooms at Ardea Country Club.

Event Rooms
Host Your Next Oldsmar Event With Us
Host a fabulous event at Ardea Country Club and enjoy the fruits of your labor along with your guests. Our private event directors help with everything from food to decorations to entertainment, and our staff makes sure your event is truly memorable. No matter what the event, we'll create the appropriate mood and take the stress out of hosting.
Start Planning Your Event
We can help with any type of event:
-Showers
-Reunions
-Birthday Parties
-Private Dinners
-Banquets
-School Parties
-Holiday Parties
-Business Meetings
-Seminars
-Rehearsal Dinners
-Bar/Bat Mitzvah
-Luncheons
-Charity Galas
-Anniversary Parties
Thank you so much for making our luncheon so special. You and your staff were wonderful. Every aspect was perfect!
- Anne S.

Tampa Meetings Have Never Been Easier
Corporate Meeting and Event Venue in Tampa, FL
Mix business with pleasure for a productive day away from the office at Ardea. Our corporate meeting and event venues provide everything you need to impress your colleagues and inspire your employees. The executive chef can provide personalized menus to fit your event, while our experienced team goes above and beyond to create a flawless event for you and your guests.
Schedule A Meeting
We provide personalized service and professional accommodations for a variety of business functions, including:
Formal Meetings | Business Dinners | Team Building Sessions | Corporate & Client Golf Outings | Employee Play Days
Thank you so much for the lovely TOWA Luncheon. The ladies all enjoyed the room, good food and great service by your staff. We'll be calling again soon!
- Donne A.

About Aaron
Aaron joined the Ardea team in January, 2022, coming to us from our sister club, Countryside, where he started his Invited career in 2017.  Aaron grew up in Dunedin and is a graduate of Warren Southern in Lake Whales, Florida. He has spent over 25 years in the Hospitality Industry and gained his experience at numerous local and national chain restaurants. Aaron has a tremendous drive and passion for all aspects of hospitality; he demonstrates that daily through his goal-oriented approach and result-driven mentality. Aaron’s goal is to ensure that Members have a phenomenal Club experience every time!  When he's not at the Club, he enjoys spending time with his wife and their 3 wonderful children.
